I need to calculate the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period (2024-02-05).

The Quick Ratio formula is:
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

Let me extract the relevant information from the balance sheet:

1. Current Assets (end amount): $9,982,261.98
2. Inventory (end amount): $0.00
3. Current Liabilities (end amount): $499,821.72

Now I'll calculate the Quick Ratio:
Quick Ratio = ($9,982,261.98 - $0.00) / $499,821.72
Quick Ratio = $9,982,261.98 / $499,821.72
Quick Ratio = 19.97

Rounding to two decimal places: 19.97
